      <head>Ernst Decsey</head>

      <div>
        <p>Austrian critic and author, studied law (as did Schenker) at Vienna University, and music
          with Bruckner (as did Schenker) and Fuchs at the Vienna Conservatory, became critic of the
            <title level="j">Grazer Tagespost</title> in 1900 taking over its editorship in 1908, in
          1920 he joined the <ref cRef="neues_wiener_tagblat">
            <title level="j">Neues Wiener Tagblatt</title>
          </ref>, resigning in 1938. He wrote books on Wolf, Bruckner, Johann Strau&#xDF;,
          Debussy, and others.</p>
      </div>
